{"version":1,"ops":[{"type":1,"author":{"id":"76484e451c8adcf68d1a41e60ab7fdf43d921282"},"timestamp":1361122728,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDU6SXNzdWUxMTA5MDQ0MQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/parrot/parrot/issues/935","origin":"github"},"title":"Calculation of available memory should respect resource limits","message":"Parrot uses an estimation of total available system memory to determine how much memory to use, and thus how often to run the GC.\n\nIt would be very useful if that estimation respected resource limits set with `ulimit` on Linux systems.\n\nCurrently parrot blows up with an OOM error message if it violates a hard ulimit, even though the available memory would be enough if parrot just GC'ed more often.","files":null}]}